Otto Name Meaning in English

What does the name Otto mean? What is the meaning of the name Otto, lucky number, lucky stone, origin and religion.

Otto is a masculine German given name and a surname. It originates as an Old High German short form (variants Audo, Odo, Udo) of Germanic names beginning in aud-, an element meaning "wealth, prosperity". The name is recorded from the 7th century (Odo, son of Uro, courtier of Sigebert III).

Otto Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Wealth Details: A more modern form of the Germanic Odo, from od, "wealth", "fortune". Gender: For both boy and girl, unisex, transgender, neutral gender Origin: German Religion: Christian Suitable for: Unisex / Gender neutral Hardness: Easy to pronounce, Otto is a short name Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Yes Syllables: 4 Letters and 1 Words
